Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Cut your @British Streaky Bacon{4} rashers in half widthways. Remove the string from the @Whole British Chicken{1} and transfer to a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Lay the bacon pieces widthways across the top of the chicken's breast.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Roast in the middle of the oven for ~{60-75%minutes} depending on size.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when the juices from the thigh run clear.

Meanwhile, pour a good glug of oil onto another baking tray and pop into your oven. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil on high heat with a pinch of @salt{}.

Peel the @potatoes{700%g}, chop them into 4cm chunks. Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook for ~{7-8%minutes} or until the edges have softened when you poke them with a #knife{}. Meanwhile, thinly slice the @Closed Cup Mushrooms{150%g}. Pick the @Tarragon{1/2} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the pan then sprinkle on the @Plain Flour{8%g}. Give your pan a shake to fluff up the potato. Take your hot baking tray out of your oven, carefully transfer your potatoes onto it in a single layer, turning in the oil. Sprinkle over a pinch of salt. Roast the potatoes on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{45-50%minutes}, turn halfway through. Wash out your saucepan we will use it again later.

== Truffled Mushroom & Tarragon Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan{} on a medium high heat. When hot, add the sliced mushrooms and cook until softened and browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @Water{300%ml}(for the sauce) and the @Wild Mushroom Paste{1}. Stir well to dissolve the paste, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer. Cook until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes} then remove from the heat.

== Broccoli ==

Once the chicken is cooked, rest it loosely wrapped in #foil{} for ~{10%minutes}. Fill the pan used to cook the potatoes with water and return to high heat. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp} and the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g}. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Add the @Creme Fraiche{150%g} to the mushroom sauce, stir well to combine, bring to the boil on a medium heat.

> TIP: Add a splash of @?water{} if the sauce needs loosening up.

Reheat anything that may have cooled. Share the broccoli between your plates. Serve the roast potatoes along side. Carve your roast chicken and serve along side. Stir the tarragon and half of the @Truffle Zest{1}(divided) into the sauce and pour over the dish. Finish by garnishing with the remaining truffle zest. Enjoy!